          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "On its way to the collimators an unpolarized proton",
                "beam is deflected in an auxiliary magnetic field by an",
                "angle of 14.2 degr. Thus the beam was purified of",
                "neutral and low energy particle admixture.",
                "Geometrically, the collimation was such that at the",
                "place of the scatterer the following conditions were",
                "fulfilled: a) the beam image on the autograph was 20 mm",
                "high and 10 mm wide and b) the horizontal plane beam",
                "divergence was equal to +-0.15 degr. Due care was taken",
                "to reduce the proton scattering effect in the",
                "collimator walls."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SCIN",
                "CEREN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered protons were",
                "registered by a telescope of 3 scintillation counters",
                "and one Cerenkov counter with a plexiglass radiator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The averaged results of the measurements of the",
                "counting rate were used to plot the angular",
                "distribution of charged secondaries. The corresponding",
                "curve   was  then  normalized to  values of the",
                "differential cross sections for the emission of",
                "charged secondaries in p+C collisions, which were",
                "obtained earlier in L.Azhgirey,J,JETP,36,1631,1959,",
                "under conditions identical with those of the present",
                "experiments. The total energy spectrum of charged",
                "secondaries, measured at 7 degr., was also normalized",
                "to a value of the differential cross section for",
                "the same angles and equal to 1.1+-0.055 b/sr."
              ]
            }
          ],
